Description: The first inmate who tested positive in mid-June was asymptomatic, was housed in a quarantine block and has since received a negative COVID-19 test and completed a 14-day quarantine. This is no longer an active case. The other three COVID-positive inmates were admitted into the jail having tested positive prior to their arrests. They were housed in Medical Isolation and two of the three have been released from custody.
Inmates cleared or released indicates the number of inmates who tested positive for COVID-19 and have either been cleared by a physician or released from custody.
